node_9.subject: Mina Chang
node_9.description: This is Mina Chang's plan for Monday February 13: 7:00 am - Wake up and complete morning routine, including getting dressed and eating breakfast., 8:00 am - Attend morning classes at Oak Hill College, engaging with peers and making new friends., 11:00 am - Grab a coffee with friends and discuss the excitement around the new male student., 12:00 pm - Attend afternoon classes, continuing to socialize during breaks., 3:00 pm - Join a study group to prepare for upcoming exams, showcasing her leadership skills while balancing social interactions., 5:00 pm - Head to gym or dance class to burn off energy and meet new people., 6:00 pm - Have dinner with her twin sister Iris and friends, making sure to catch up on everyone’s day., 7:00 pm - Attend a social mixer organized by the college to meet the new male student and make her presence known., 9:00 pm - Participate in a fun group activity with friends, such as karaoke or games, maintaining the lively atmosphere., 10:30 pm - Wind down and reflect on the day, perhaps journaling her thoughts or secrets before bed., 11:00 pm - Go to bed, excited for the adventures of the next day..
